cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.DC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with dynamic versions of geometric set cover and hitting set, which are fundamental problems in computational geometry and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also presents efficient data structures for maintaining optimal solutions, which involves designing algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DC (Discrete Computational Geometry) as possible categories. Finally, the paper presents approximation algorithms, which involves theoretical computer science and optimization, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category as well.
